review_blob: Lives up to the hype. Pours opaque black with a mid size tan head. Cinnabun on the nose. Cinnamon Coffee taste with a creamy mouth feel. Breakfast or Dessert.
Chocolate aroma, pours pitch black with a light tan head. Taste: chocolate coffee. Creamy mouth feel. Very sweet, did not want bottle to end.

2008 from the Cellar at Brick Store Pub in Decatur, Georgia. Poured a milky dark brown with a thin beige head. Aroma of chocolate and booze. Low carbonation with the aging. Chocolate raisin up front boozey back end.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: a 2006 out of the cellar at Brick Store Pub in Decatur. Poured a light brown with a minimal cream head. Aroma of Black Cherry Vanilla. Flavor was a nice balance of sweetness and sour.
On draft at Closed for Business in Charleston, SC Pours dark brown/black with a mid sized beige head. Raisin on the nose with hints of booze. Chocolatey rum flavor. Not bad but not impressed
Had this on draft at Daniel Island Grill immediately following the drive down. Pours a nice burnt orange/gold. well carbonated. Citrus hop flavor with tinges of yeast. My first from Holy City. Wow
beer_name: Holy City Slanted Porch Pale Ale

review_blob: Sampled at Closed for Business in Charleston, SC. Poured a burnt orange. Aroma was straight citrus hops. Citrus hop flavor with a dry finish.
Sampled at Closed for Business in Charleston, SC. Poured a golden haze with a medium head simliar to steamed milk. Aroma of spiced citrus.Dry taste with citrus notes.

review_blob: Did a linear tasting with a 2012 found at Laura Alberts on Daniel Island, SC and the 2013 from Ale Yeah! Decatur, GA. The 2012 completely lost its hop flavor and produced a beer with no bite that was very sweet. The 2013 was hoppier then hell and spicy. 2 completely different beers.
